principles, namely: family, intimacy, close friendship, and camaraderie-&-solidarity.

'''Third''', and perhaps most importantly, the true human needs that are satisfied by
morally good-&-right relationships within these four basic kinds are fully in line and in
broadly Kantian dignitarian synchrony with what can be regarded as the meaning of
rational human life itself—the individual and collective pursuit of principled
authenticity37—and therefore they’re essentially connected with what makes lives like
ours worth living."


